{"type":"text","timestamp":1773245207363,"sessionID":"ses_3225b056affeIKEEihnMYwMnTu","part":{"id":"prt_cdda686790019V9m7LA0J5RhFT","sessionID":"ses_3225b056affeIKEEihnMYwMnTu","messageID":"msg_cdda67b760013PfVneh3FiC23Q","type":"text","text":"## Subtask 2 & 3: Graceful error on invalid YAML schema + Wrap YAML parse errors\n\nBoth subtasks 2 and 3 are about `loadFeatures()`. The issue is:\n1. If YAML is valid but schema is wrong (e.g., `features: not-an-array`), the code crashes with \"Attempted to assign to readonly property\" when trying to normalize. \n2. If YAML is corrupted/malformed, the raw YAML library error is shown.\n\nI'll wrap the entire `loadFeatures()` function with proper error handling for both cases.","time":{"start":1773245207363,"end":1773245207363}}}
